      • getLexicalValue

        public String getLexicalValue()
        Description copied from interface: DatatypeConstant
        Returns the lexical value of the data value, i.e. a string that encodes a specific value based on the value's datatype. Note that there can be several strings that represent the same value, depending on the rules of the datatype, and that there the value used here does not have to be a canonical representation.
        Specified by:
        getLexicalValue in interface DatatypeConstant
        Returns:
        a non-null string

      • getRdfLiteralString

        public String getRdfLiteralString(boolean useAbbreviations)
        Description copied from interface: DatatypeConstant
        Returns a string representation of this value that conforms to RDF serialisation formats such as Turtle. Turtle supports some abbreviations for common types, e.g., by leaving the type away for xsd:string literals, which can be enabled or disabled through the functions parameter.
        Specified by:
        getRdfLiteralString in interface DatatypeConstant
        Parameters:
        useAbbreviations - if true, the result may use Turtle-style abbreviations to shorten the output where supported; otherwise the literal will always be serialised in full
        Returns:
        RDF-style string serialisation of the value
